      "lesson title": "AI in Drug Discovery: Data Integrity Risks",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Artificial intelligence is transforming drug discovery, helping researchers analyse vast datasets and identify promising compounds far more quickly than traditional methods allow. However, the quality of the data fed into these AI systems has a direct impact on the reliability of the results they produce. In this lesson, we explore the key data integrity risks that arise when AI is used in drug discovery, including issues such as biased datasets, incomplete records, and poor data governance practices. You will learn how these risks can lead to flawed research outcomes, wasted resources, and potentially harmful consequences for patients. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of why maintaining high-quality, well-managed data is essential to responsible and effective AI-driven research.",
